  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: edge-case coverage gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence spans the nominal operating envelope (2–5 L/min, 1500–3000 RPM); high-shear-stress regions and near-stall low-flow boundary conditions named in the COU are noted as studied separately but that work is not linked or included herein.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-rh-criterion",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-cfd-identifies-worst-case-hemolysis",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-rans-sst",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-validation-nominal-flowspeeds",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-piv-measurements-bulk-range",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-index-nominal"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device, including high-shear-stress regions near the volute cutwater and near-stall low-flow boundary conditions (≤1 L/min) where erythrocyte damage is clinically most critical. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-01-2Lmin-2000rpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Validation point 1: 2 L/min, 2000 RPM — nominal mid-range",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index compared against in-vitro measurement at 2 L/min, 2000 RPM. RH = 0.84 (within acceptance criterion). Shear stress distribution in bulk impeller passage agrees with PIV within 8%. Operating point is well within the nominal clinical envelope; no proximity to volute cutwater high-shear zone or low-flow stall boundary."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-02-3Lmin-2500rpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Validation point 2: 3 L/min, 2500 RPM — nominal design point",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index compared against in-vitro measurement at 3 L/min, 2500 RPM (device design point). RH = 0.79. Velocity profiles at impeller exit match LDV data within 6%. This is the most thoroughly validated operating condition; bulk-region shear stresses are representative of typical CPB perfusion."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-03-4Lmin-2500rpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Validation point 3: 4 L/min, 2500 RPM — nominal high-flow",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index compared against in-vitro measurement at 4 L/min, 2500 RPM. RH = 0.91. Pressure-rise prediction within 3% of bench measurement. Flow is fully attached; no recirculation zones. Operating point remains in the nominal bulk-flow regime, away from the near-stall low-flow boundary explicitly identified in the COU."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-04-3Lmin-3000rpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Validation point 4: 3 L/min, 3000 RPM — elevated speed nominal",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index at elevated rotational speed. RH = 0.88. Turbulent dissipation rates in bulk passages match PIV-derived estimates within 12%. The volute cutwater region, where the COU explicitly calls out high-shear-stress as clinically critical, was not included in the validation measurement domain; edge-case shear characterisation in that sub-region is noted as addressed in a separate study (reference withheld pending publication)."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-05-5Lmin-3000rpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Validation point 5: 5 L/min, 3000 RPM — upper nominal boundary",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index at the upper edge of the nominal clinical flow range. RH = 0.93. This is the highest-flow validation point and sits at the upper boundary of the nominal envelope. No validation data collected below 2 L/min; near-stall low-flow conditions (≤1 L/min) referenced in the COU as highest hemolytic risk were not tested. Edge cases studied separately."
    }
  ],
