      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst qualification documented separately.",
      "rationale": "Formal use-error assessment not required at MRL 2. Analyst credentials and training records are on file with the sponsor. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; turbulence model selection justified by literature precedent.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published FDA pump benchmark studies showing best-in-class performance for rotating blood-contacting devices. Formal model-form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; input parameter sources documented in simulation plan.",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs derived from FDA-published CAD files. Fluid properties from published blood-analogue characterisation data. Formal input uncertainty propagation not required at MRL 2. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Minimum of three independent experimental replicates per operating point; coefficient of variation < 10% for hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "Three independent in-vitro runs performed at each of the five nominal validation operating points (15 total experiments). Coefficient of variation for hemolysis index ranged from 3.1% to 8.7% across points, all within the 10% acceptance criterion. Sample adequacy confirmed for the nominal range. No replicate samples were collected at near-stall or high-shear-stress boundary conditions; edge cases studied separately per project plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Dimensionless flow coefficient and head coefficient match between CFD and experiment within 5% at each validation point.",
      "rationale": "Flow coefficient (Q/ND³) and head coefficient (gH/N²D²) computed for all five nominal validation points. CFD and experimental values agree within 3.4% for flow coefficient and 4.1% for head coefficient across all points. Equivalency confirmed for the nominal operating envelope. Equivalency at the near-stall low-flow boundary (≤1 L/min) was not evaluated; that regime is acknowledged in the COU as clinically critical but is addressed in a separate study not linked to this evidence package. Gradation 2 met for assessed range."
    }
