    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation levels for MRL 2. The six not-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3 guidance for MRL 2. Validation evidence across the five nominal operating points demonstrates consistent agreement between CFD predictions and in-vitro measurements (mean RH deviation 7.2%, GCI < 4%). The assessment team accepts the model for the COU decision on worst-case hemolysis identification within the nominal clinical operating envelope. High-shear-stress regions near the volute cutwater and near-stall low-flow boundary conditions named in the COU are noted as studied separately; that supplementary evidence is not yet available for review but is not considered necessary for the present MRL 2 acceptance decision.",
